<br>
1) Target choice, might be bad, MB is fast damage wich is perfect for low hp kunark dragons, sont and such. To do it with mage pets you'd need to chain cast epics, wich is possible and could work. But imho choice of target for team mage should be a bit different. (for example sontalak would need an insane number of chain casting mages hehe). <br>
<br>
So imho your best bet as team mage would be different targets (pretty sure the 3 kunark dragons could be done with a group or 2 of mages but sont and such might be hard). Thing is team mage could prolly own most dungeons named (lord bob, vaniki, shroum king, prog/tola if trak ain't up, lots of stuff in luclin, chardok named and royals) much more efficiently than wiz, a puller, 1 cleric and the mages can handle the rest (can actualy live without puller/cleric for some of those).<br>
<br>
2) The valiant companion dispell thing... we have the perfect tool to prevent that, I already posted a few times but will again. @#%$ BUFFS! People been doing it since naggy/vox days, it worked then, it still works today, it works on players, it works on pets. Here`s simple way to do it.<br>
<br>
1) summon bunch of lev ring<br>
2) summon pet, imediately lev him<br>
3) put regular buffs on pet<br>
4) engage dragon/boss/dispelling and fear casting fire beetles<br>
5) when pet get dispelled, refresh lev<br>
6) loot dragon/boss/dispelling and fear casting fire beetles<br>
7) dance, sing and get drunk<br>
<br>
key step is #5<br>
<br>
3) For aoe mob, don't bring a healer, bring lotsa malachite and chain pets. Also using pet innate resists (those that ain't broke) can help more with aoe than healers.<br>
